CONDUIT_NAME.id: The spell ID of the conduit -- This is what should be used when identifying if a player has that conduit and also for searching for it on WoWHead or similiar.
CONDUIT_NAME.name: The name of the conduit
CONDUIT_NAME.icon: The icon string of the conduit
CONDUIT_NAME.type: The type of the conduit - potency, endurance, finesse
CONDUIT_NAME.covenantID: The ID of the covenant, as defined in src/game/shadowlands/COVENANTS.ts
CONDUIT_NAME.soulbindConduitID: The unique ID of that conduit that is the same regardless of the rank
CONDUIT_NAME.conduitItemID: The item ID of the item giving you access to the conduit. Used when searching wowhead with item= searches

spellModifierByRanks.rankInteger: The effect it has on the spell it affects, the value can be in milliseconds, percentage numbers etc - that's up to the maintainer to figure out. Note rank 1 is index 0 - this is also the case in the game data.
